{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b8744800-3dbf-4bad-a4e3-fabfc5ababbe","content":"You're all set. Run your tests in hot-reload mode with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a watch-style session. When a test fails, you edit your code (test or production), save the file, and the runner **automatically re-runs** affected tests without a full rebuild — using .NET Hot Reload under the hood.\n\n**Key points:**\n- No extra configuration needed beyond the package reference you already have.\n- The session stays open; press `Ctrl+C` to exit.\n- Only changed code is reapplied, so iteration is near-instant.\n\nThis gives you a tight red → green feedback loop without waiting for full `dotnet build` cycles each time.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9d8a416e-3102-4c2a-b17c-0ddd33ad54bd","outputTokens":162,"requestId":"BC22:223B6B:1DD8100:212A024:69FA9802"},"id":"6da091a6-baaa-40ea-982a-cfae943ea195","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:23:20.938Z","parentId":"124c8fc5-b020-44c2-b4e4-14bcbabeadaa"}
